description:
Deadpool and Kane settle their differences in the most logical way: A fight to the death. Sabretooth leaves a message for Deadpool... In blood!

Sabretooth is getting to intense for his superiors to control. Vanessa is having troubles with her powers. Deadpool and Kane settle their differences in the only way they know how, a fight to the death. Deadpool returns to Vanessa but finds a message left by Sabretooth. Vanessa is dying and the message is left in her blood.
name: Intensive Care

description:
Vanessa's dead. Deadpool is furious and goes to find Sabretooth to avenge her.

Deadpool tracks Sabretooth down and tries to avenge Vanessa's death. But he is prevented by the director of Weapon X and is melted away by a toxic haze to almost nothingness. IS he dead?... I'd assume not because the comic continues the next month.
name: Flatline

first_appearance_locations.name: New Charles Xavier School for Mutants

location_credits.name: New Charles Xavier School for Mutants

description:
Deadpool wakes up and finds out he is dead! But of course, he must cause trouble... Even from the grave.

Deadpool wakes up and discovers he's dead and witnessing his own funeral. Both enemies and friends came to pay their respects; including his on-again, off-again enemy/ally, Bullseye; former love interest, Siryn; and Weasel and Blind Al. Of course, Deadpool being Deadpool, causes trouble, even while dead. He posesses Weasel, who is guiding Al, and leads her into an open grave. He then possess Kid Deadpool, who doodled on his picture in his coffin, and has him pinch Juggernaut, begin an outright brawl. He then goes to the afterlife and, right before he gets busy with Death, is ressurected by T-Ray, who triggers the resurrectionby urinating on Deadpool's grave.
name: Funeral For A Freak - part 1

description: Diana encounters Jonny Double, a private detective who prods her into a fight (which she wins) to test her prowess, and then offers her a job. Double is currently employed by nightclub magnate Fellows Dill, the “dean of beautiful women”. A fanatic religious / moralist organization called The Tribunal is out to murder him for his embodiment of values with which they disagree. He feels that The Tribunal’s assassins will be on the lookout for male bodyguards like Double, but not for a beautiful female like Diana. At first she refuses his offer, but when Dill offers to finance an operation that will return I-Ching’s sight, she agrees. The Tribunal strikes while Dill, Diana, and Double are travelling on a private train car, gassing both Diana and Double unconscious, though Dill escapes. Diana and Double are placed on trial by The Tribunal’s hierarchy, and are condemned to death for their involvement with Dill. Jonny offers to bring back Dill in exchange for their lives, with Diana staying as a hostage. The Tribunal agree, with a three-day deadline. When three days pass without Double’s return, an executioner is sent to Diana’s cell, but she knocks him unconscious, takes his keys, and frees herself. She fights her way past guards and, seeing Tribunal members with Double in tow, takes a guard’s robe and follows them in disguise. Double admits to The Tribunal that he was unable to find Dill, but offers himself as sacrifice in place of Diana. Diana attacks the guards and she and Jonny make an escape from The Tribunal’s stronghold. Minutes later, Jonny and Diana are about to share a kiss when Double is grazed by a gunshot. The gunman is Fellows Dill, holding a pistol, with an insane look on his face.
name: Tribunal of Fear - Part One

description: Diana knocks Fellows Dill down and Jonny Double takes his gun. Dill proves to be insane, and they trail his footprints to what appears to be a cabin in the mountains, but what is in reality the anteroom of a fabulous hideout burrowed into the mountain. Two Tribunal members appear in a helicopter. Jonny and Diana defeat them and take their craft, but soon find that the controls are locked on it and it flies them by remote control to Fellows Dill’s estate. Once there, they are attacked by members of Dr. Cyber’s gang. Jonny is subdued, and Diana vaults inside the mansion, falling through a trapdoor into a dungeon full of beautiful women. Diana realizes that Dr. Cyber is behind the caper, having recognized Cyber’s insignia on her gang members. But Cyber knocks Diana unconscious with electric bolts from a device in the ceiling. Diana awakens to find herself chained beside Jonny, with a steel-masked Dr. Cyber sizing them both up. Cyber tells them that she escaped the destruction of her undersea fortress through a safety route, rebuilt her organization, admittedly “was mad”, and “established The Tribunal to destroy all who trafficked in human beauty!” Then she discovered a mind-control serum, which she used on Dill. Now, her objective is to have her brain transplanted by her associate Dr. Moon, late an ally of Ra’s Al Ghul, into the body of a beautiful woman. The lovely captives Diana saw were candidates for Cyber’s new housing. Now, she admits she wants to be housed in Diana’s body. When Moon administers anesthetic gas to Diana, she suspends her breathing by yoga techniques and remains awake, faking unconsciousness. Then she attacks Cyber and her guards, and, when Cyber attacks with a scalpel, judo-tosses her. Cyber impales herself on the scalpel. Diana frees Jonny, and they embrace, ready to leave.
name: Tribunal of Fear - Part Two

description: Guest-starring Lobo. After the coolest and most violent fight scene in the history of graphic storytelling, Etrigan and Lobo team up to top it off by destroying the Earth!
name: Lobo's Pal the Demon Versus-- Lobo! Surprise Appearance by Lobo

description: Lobo and the Demon...they're just the duo you want fighting for control of a plummeting atomic bomb. Not even that cosmic know-it-all the Phantom Stranger can influence the destructive outcome of their battle!
name: The Demon Vs. Lobo It's a Blast!

description:
In this epilogue to "The Old Dog," we peer into HITMAN's future. Sixty years from now, a mysterious stranger in Noonan's Bar shares a bloody, legendary tale of Tommy Monaghan and his friends.

In a story set some time in the future, a mysterious strange sets the story straight for several naive college students. Including the horrible things Tommy had down to revenge himself for Sean Noonan's death.
name: The Old Dog, Epilogue

description:
Elektra faces off with the men who honed her into a weapon: the evil clan of ninjas known as The Hand!

The Hand clashes against their most powerful creations, assassins who once belonged to their sept.
name: Everything Old Is New Again Part 4

description:
Elektra vs. The Hand: The final showdown for her freedom!

The Hand pushed Elektra too far by killing her sensei. They then took Locke hostage, enraging her even further.

Elektra and the Hand meet up in the Mojave desert for a "fight to the death" battle.

Who will win? Who will lose? Has Elektra training paid off?
name: Everything Old Is New Again Part 5

description:
A new creative team jumps on board for a look at Elektra's impact as a killer! The stunning assassin is seen through the eyes of her mark, taking you on a journey through a dying man's last day. Well, his last day if Elektra has her way! Join us as the new team of novelist Robert Rodi, the fan-favorite Wolverine art team of Sean Chen and Tom Palmer, and new cover artist Bill Sienkiewicz take Elektra on a journey you won’t soon forget!

Has Elektra ever missed a hit? Apparently so. But she's back at it. A millionare who's gotten away too many times is about to get what he has coming. The blood hungry Elektra is coming for him. Find out if she gets the hit or will he get away another time.
name: The Mark

description: Witness a deadly game of cat and mouse in glorious detail as we watch Elektra systematically take down her hit.
name: The Job

description:
Part 2 of "Checkout," the crossover with CHECKMATE! The prison hasn't been built that can hold the Outsiders for long — and that includes Checkmate's Alpine HQ, as Nightwing leads an attempt to break free from house arrest!

This story continues in Checkmate #14.
name: Checkout (Part 2)

description:
Overview

Grifter and Midnighter are in it up to their necks as the City of Lights becomes Beachhead Francois for a deadly extraterrestrial invasion. What started as a routine covert op turns into an intergalactic bloodbath with no mission objective other than survival.

Picking up immediately from the end of last issue, Grifter, Midnighter and Zee face off against a seemingly endless flood of aliens in Paris, France. Grifter, as usual, jumps, guns blazing, straight into battle leaving Midnighter with Zee. The time alone (well, not alone, the monsters are still attacking) gives Zee a chance to drop cryptic clues about what's going on. She tells Midnighter that he is at the center of a synergy and the tentacled creatures seek him for the same reason she does. Midnighter again asks her who she is, but her reply is simply, "I am Zee." Midnighter promises to hunt down Jenny for the rest of her unnaturally long life if he finds out that she's connected to any of this. Before he can attempt to pry more answers from Zee, a helpless woman is attacked by an alien and he is forced to save her. While Midnighter fights more monsters, Zee, who had jumped away and is now perched safely atop a building, talks to him. She tells Midnighter that he is an enhanced being, but even he has limits. He was kidnapped (read issue 1) to assess those limits. The master of the creatures he's fighting has studied him. This prompts Midnighter to ask Zee which side she's on but she tells him that it's not that simple. Midnighter insists that it is but Zee goes on to talk about something seemingly unrelated: Midnighter's powers. She explains that his neural upgrades allow him to work through a million scenarios a second and he sees each possible encounter and reacts with the best option. Midnighter says she's right and she responds by saying that's only true if he processes probabilities faster than his opponents. If the enemy is one second faster, can find the one scenario he hasn't reached yet, his enhancements are useless. As she says this, Midnighter is outmaneuvered by an alien and struck. She tells him that his ability has created a necessary level of confidence, but confidence leads to arrogance, and arrogance leads to complacency. While she's speaking, two more aliens grab Midnighter from behind and the original attacker shoots a tentacle through Midnighters torso and beats him mercilessly. Zee tells Midnighter that only one thing can save him, a significant variable. Grifter.

The red-masked, gun-wielding Wildcat jumps over the alien attacking Midnighter and kills all the monsters around him. After they die, green "brain bugs", smaller, ghost-like bugs inside the aliens, scuttle out of the dead bodies and teleport away. With Midnighter now relatively safe and Grifter holding the bugs back with his guns, Zee decides to step in. She pushes Grifter away and tells him that the two of them will serve. Zee, rapidly losing her normal form and turning into something with skin like the aliens, is seemingly destroyed when a giant tentacle smacks down directly on her. The few remaining aliens all run away and Grifter drags Midnighter away from the battlefield.

Soon after the duo are gone, Apollo, Swift, The Engineer and The Doctor arrive on the scene. They can find no sign of Midnighter (and they're not looking for Grifter) but they find a giant hole in the ground. Apollo flies down inside of it but finds nothing.

In the sewers some distance away, Midnighter heals the hole in his chest along with his broken jaw and arm while Grifter annoys him. When they get up they see Zee and she tells them there's a planet to save.
name: Uncivil Union

description:
While Diana Prince is consulting with Inspector David McLean of the Hong Kong police, the island is rocked by an earthquake.

Diana is racing against as Dr. Cyber threatens to use his earthquake machines to level Hong Kong.
name: Earth-Quaker! Part Two

description:
I-Ching goes to Red China to find his daughter.

Diana, I-Ching and Patrick McGuire help a Chinese village flee from communist China.
name: Red For Death!

description:
While on a trip to Paradise Island, Diana gets lost in another dimension.

While attempting to transport themselves to Paradise Island, Diana and Leda are trapped in an alternate dimension. Diana is captured and made to fight in an arena with a barbarian prince, Ranagor.
name: Detour

description: As they prepare for battle Diana explains her recent history to Ranagor.
name: Detour - Part Two

description:
The North Ambrians take heavy losses in assaulting Castle Skull until Diana devises cannons for them to breach the walls.

Wonder Woman, Ranagor and his army lay siege to Castle Skull.
name: Assault on Castle Skull

description:
Mrs. Petrucci, mother of Diana's friend Tony, asks for Diana''s help, revealing that her daughter Angela was rendered comatose three years ago when she had some punch at a party held by Tony's Vietnam War buddy Eddie Dean.

Diana tries to help a friend solve a mystery and ends up stopping him from murdering.
name: Angela

description:
While on vacation in the European country of Daldonia, Diana Prince finds herself the victim of a kidnapping attempt!

Diana is on vacation where she is mistaken for the country's soon-to-be-married princess. When the princess gets kidnapped it is up to Diana to take her place while trying to find the kidnappers.
name: The Prisoner

description:
Diana Prince and I-Ching pick up two motorists having car trouble--and soon discover their new passengers are actually escaped convicts intent on holding them hostage!

Diana and I-Ching are forced to seek shelter in a remote inn during a snowstorm but all is not as it appears.
name: The House That Wasn't

description: A man dying of gunshot wounds stumbles into Diana's boutique, revealing that he is a secret agent for a government agency and investigating a plot to assassinate the Koronian ambassador.
name: Target for Today?

description:
Part 2 of the 5-part "Kid Amazo!" The Justice League are two steps behind Amazo and his "son" with an urgent need to reach the youth before he succumbs to his "father's" evil programming.

Standing in the remains of Professor Ivo's lab, the Justice League discusses what they'll do with the new Kid Amazo. Flash, Green Lantern John Stewart and Martian Manhunter want to strike right away, destroying the cyborg before it attacks or can even choose to be evil. Batman thinks they should wait and see, but if any action is to be taken, it should be to reprogram it and not destroy it. Wonder Woman and Superman agree with Batman that they should wait to see if Kid Amazo becomes good or evil.

In a house somewhere else, Professor Ivo and Amazo go over their plans for Kid Amazo. Amazo wants to cause an earthquake at his "son's" school to show him the power he could have as well as force him to fight alongside him if the JLA comes. Ivo approves his plan so Amazo immediately attempts it. Amazo finds Kid Amazo as he's about to meet his girlfriend for a movie. She hasn't arrived yet so Kid Amazo tells his father to leave before she gets there since he doesn't want her to see him. Amazo seems hurt as he tunnels underground to start the earthquake. Kid Amazo follows Amazo underground, but isn't exactly sure why. Amazo sets off the earthquake and both of them fly into the sky to see the effects of his work. Kid Amazo is torn. He doesn't know if he should save the humans or let them die. Making up his mind he flies below the earth and reverses what Amazo did. When he tunnels back to the surface he sees a cop. He tries to fly away but he causes the cop to shoot himself. Feeling remorse, Kid Amazo takes he cop to the hospital and along the way he figures out how he's going to handle the Amazo situation. He's going to make him mad.

At another location, the JLA are still talking about Amazo. Diana says that Kid Amazo's girlfriend might be in danger but Bruce says tries to assure her that the girl won't be in harm's way. J'onn reveals that he's been watching Kid Amazo and reading his mind. He tells Bruce and Diana that the cyborg has been training, practicing using his powers, in a desert. He also tells them that according to what he picked up with a mind scan, Kid Amazo might be insane.
name: Kid Amazo, Part Two: Man & Superman

description:
More all-out international action with Marvel's sexiest assassin! It's war in Iraq over the mysterious artifact known as the Scorpio Key! And Elektra's right in the middle of it, battling for her life against a surprise enemy! Plus, the espionage agency known as S.H.I.E.L.D. has a new secret- and it may cost Nick Fury his life!

Elektra is contracted by S.H.I.E.L.D. to take out Middle Eastern terrorist Saddam Abed Dasam and Hydra who Saddam hired. S.H.I.E.L.D. wants Elektra to assassinate Saddam with no one finding out and take a mysterious box that is in Saddam's possession. For these Nick Fury promises, Elektra`s past sins will be forgotten. While Stanley and a fellow S.H.I.E.L.D. member go out for a walk in Baghdad they are attacked by Hydra but are saved by Elektra. She says there is a traitor among S.H.I.E.L.D. and things escalate into a murder or what appears to be.
name: The Book of Samurai

description:
S.H.I.E.L.D. discovers that not even the world’s largest surveillance agency can control or predict Elektra. Elektra discovers that she doesn’t suffer traitors well. What is the Scorpio Key?

A devastetad SHIELD agent thinks that he killed Elektra and that their operation to kill Saddam Abed Dasam and retrive the mysterious box is now compromised. Nick Fury informs him that Elektra has just used a ninja mind scramble on him. Fury pushes Elektra to accept the mission by threats and revealing what is in the box. A traitor inside SHIELD informs HYDRA about Elektra and in turn she learns that the object in the box is the Scorpio Key. Elektra has made the traitor and leaves her stranded in the desert.

Continuing the blazing hot new Knights series by Brian Michael Bendis (ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN) and Chuck Austen (King of the Hill)! On a mission of asassination in Iraq, Elektra receives a shocking offer from the terrorist organization known as Hydra! But it's S.H.I.E.L.D. agent Stanley Dreyfuss who'll have to sort out the players in this deadly game of espionage, that is, if enough of them are left alive!

More all-out international action with Marvel's sexiest assassin! It's war in Iraq over the mysterious artifact known as the Scorpio Key! And Elektra's right in the middle of it, battling for her life against a surprise enemy! Plus: the espionage agency known as S.H.I.E.L.D. has a new secret -- and it may cost Nick Fury his life!

It's apocalypse in Iraq as Marvel's deadliest, sexiest ninja finally finds the Scorpio Key! But Nick Fury of S.H.I.E.L.D. is also after the Key, and so is the international terrorist organization known as Hydra! When the dust clears, who will Elektra entrust with the deadliest weapon known to man?

Elektra doesn't talk much normally, but this issue, she's even more quiet and deadly than ever! While delivering a message to Matt Murdock, Elektra encounters a very dangerous young woman. How will this new assassin affect the lives of Elektra and the Man Without Fear?

Elektra finally went to see Daredevil, but he wasn't there. Something Elektra wasn't looking for was a fight.

Free from the clutches of S.H.I.E.L.D., Elektra returns to the life of a freelance mercenary. But how do you contact an assassin-for-hire, anyway? For one wealthy Greek heiress, the answer may mean life or death!
Elektra has received her assignment: deliver four men to a remote Greek island. But what does the island's mysterious mistress want with these men, and will the sexy assassin follow her wishes?

She's faced death and killed dozens of men- but you've never seen Elektra like this before! Someone has cut her off from her livelihood, and she'll have to find out who it is- that is, if she doesn't go mad first! It's gut-wrenching drama by writer Greg Rucka, with stunning art by penciller Carlo Pagulayan and inker extraordinaire Danny Miki!

Hungry for work, and fighting without being paid. Elektra was looking for work. But that's wasn't all she was after; she was looking for blood.
name: Introspect Part 1

description:
Jeremy Locke finds it difficult to ‘sleep tight’…especially when trapped in his bedroom by the deadly Elektra! The trail of blood has led to this- a psychotic face off for the truth. Will Elektra be able to make the kill shot? Or will her own personal crisis lead her down a path less familiar?

The entire story takes place in the bedroom of Jeremy Locke, where he faces Elektra trying to kill him, while Elektra faces her crysis.
name: Introspect Conclusion

description: Locke may have his doubts about Elektra, but now he’s committed to her reformation! Under the tutelage of a new master, will the assassin become a defender instead of a killer?
name: Standing Outside the Temple in the Rain Part 1

description: Elektra must prove her worth to Drake, a sagacious master of martial arts. But can an assassin truly reform, especially one so steeped in blood? Elektra thought she knew all there was to being a survivor, a killer. But the mysterious Drake has reawakened her to new possibilities…and a new future.
name: Standing Outside the Temple in the Rain Part 2

description: Drake has agreed to take on Elektra as a student, but is our assassin ready for her humbling assignments? The Hand emerges once more, determined to reclaim a former pupil.
name: Everything Old Is New Again Part 1

description: Drake encourages Elektra to recall her early training with Stick. The Hand becomes ever more vigilant in tracking down what once was theirs. A glimpse into Drake’s death-defying past!
name: Everything Old Is New Again Part 2

description:
The Hand wants their "property" back--but are they up to the task of claiming it?

Perfect Death and Betrayer are well armed and waiting for them...
name: Everything Old Is New Again Part 3

description:
Overview

The new series art team of Carlo Barberi (OUTSIDERS) and Drew Geraci (52, NIGHTWING) debuts to kick off a brand new arc that will feature loads of guest stars from the Wildstorm Universe! In the wake of the catastrophic confrontation with the power-mad minds of Tabula Rasa, the Gen13 kids find themselves trusting their deadliest enemy. No WildStorm fan will want to miss it!
name: Road Trip, Part 1 - Club Kids

description: Tommy takes an a contract to track down and take out a scientist who can create zombies. Unfortunately the man is one step ahead of them and the Gotham Aquarium is over-taken. And the animals are escaping their cages...
name: Zombie Night at the Gotham Aquarium Part One of Two

description:
"Ace of Killers" Part 1! A demonic enemy comes knocking for Tommy Monaghan's soul: Hell's personal hitman, the Mawzir! But how does Catwoman fit into the creature's sudden appearance?

The Mawzir is back to kill Tommy Monaghan, anyone who is with him, nearby police officers...plus he has an army of Mafia mooks to back him up.
name: Ace of Killers, Part One

description: The Mudpack has trapped the Dark Knight, and only his former comrade from the Outsiders, Looker, stands a chance of saving him. "The Mudpack" part 2.
name: Mud Pack Part 2 of 4: Heart of Steel, Feet of Clay

description: The exploits of a professional poker player suddenly thrown into a high-stakes game of mythical proportions continue. One by one, Joey Martin's friends turn up in his tiny apartment-cum-afterlife, in forms that represent their horrible deaths, from a box of ashes to a pile of alligator dung. Meanwhile, the competition between Heaven and Hell continues as Bill and Michael kidnap Joey's girlfriend while Hell Mary tries to seduce Joey into selling her the souls.
name: House Rules or The Inevitable Fate of Sidekicks

description: Vegas is in flames, his girlfriend is about to get tortured, and his annoying friends (now trapped in hideous forms following their horrendous deaths) are crowding his humble apartment/afterlife. But nothing can stop Joey Martin from raising the stakes as he plays the last hand of high-end celestial poker.
name: Full House or No Way to Treat a Lady

description: The bizarre game of high-stakes celestial poker comes to a close. Arch-rivals Bill, the Angel of the Lord, and Hell Mary join forces to up their odds in the final round. But when the players reveal their hands, there's a lot more in the cards for Joey Martin (not to mention his dead girlfriend) as Chaos Monkeys, Minotaurs and poker chips converge on Cloud 9.
name: Stacking the Deck or A Clean Well-Lit Place

description: Inside Sarah's 'Alice in Wonderland' inspired outback
Ending the storyline with Iago the banana slug inside Sarah's Alice-in-Wonderland inspired outback
In this issue, Julie tells her son Mark the beginning of the story of "Megan", a teenage girl confused about her sexual identity. Megan's story will continue in Maxx #34.
In this issue, Sarah finally resurfaces after she seemingly exploded during the adventure in her Outback, only now she's stuck in the body of a giant Isz.
This issue tells the story of Glory, the teenage girl taken advantage of earlier in the series by Mr. Gone, now older and wiser and very insecure.
This bizarre stand-alone issue picks up the story of Dude and Mickey from Friends of Maxx #1, now about 10 years older and surprisingly still together; but thrown into an extremely unusual situation.
name: The Love for Three Oranges

description: This mature-readers tagged issue picks up Julie's story of 'Meghan' from a few issues back, following through on her discovery of her sexual identity.

To borrow the tagline off the final issue of Peter Milligan's 'X-Statix': "Downbeat yet Strangely Moving Final Issue!" The universe is coming to an end and Mr. Gone is guiding each cast member into their next ideal outback reality.

While Astra's off on an adventure, the First Family tears through their rogues gallery in an effort to find her.

While the first family is looking all around the globe to find her, Astra First is living her first adventure alone, learning how to play hopscotch at a nearby school, and discovering what a normal life is like.
name: Adventures in Other Worlds

description: Kicking off the 5-part "Kid Amazo!" Professor Ivo and Amazo have hatched an unusual experiment that just might mean the downfall of the Justice League—but could their experiment turn on them? Meet the robot Amazo's only child: Kid Amazo!
name: Kid Amazo, Part One: Into the Abyss

description:
Late at night in Las Vegas, the tattoo parlor is about to close. Enter the tall, dark and stunningly beautiful stranger ...

Vampirella strips off and lays on the couch, ready to become the tattooist's greatest masterpiece. As he works, she tells him of her nativity and her mission. Obsessed with his art he hardly notices what she is saying. He discovers that he has tattooed the face of his wife on Vampirella's back ... the wife he murdered several years back.

Vampirella was present when the wife died, tasted her blood and absorbed her memories.

Justice is meted out with a twist.
name: Ink

description:
CAPCOM's legendary action-horror franchise, DARKSTALKERS, arrives to comics at last! In this first issue of the new ongoing monthly series, the blood-curdling tales of MORRIGAN, DEMITRI, FELICIA and company begin with the sighting of a star--a sign, some say, of the world's impending doom. But are the DARKSTALKERS there to bring about that terrible end, or thwart it? The answer starts here in the first action- packed, blood-drenched issue! PLUS! Fan-Favorite artist JOE MADUREIRA provides an exclusive JAW-DROPPING Power Foil cover featuring everyone's favorite sexy succubus, MORRIGAN! Acclaimed artist MARK (AMAZING FANTASY, CABLE/DEADPOOL) BROOKS provides a variant cover and backup story!

The main story of this issue is collected in the trade paperback.

There's also a back-up story with art provided by variant cover artist Mark Brooks.
name: Chapter 01

description:
Overview

Zero Girl is the story of a high-school misfit coming of age. Young Amy Snooster -- weirdness magnet that she is -- never has been the most popular girl in school. She can speak to insects and believes that circles are good and squares evil. Awkward and different, she doesn't quite fit into any social circle, and she likes it that way. But strange things seem to happen when Amy is around - the spontaneous appearance of puddles of water, for instance -- and it has made her the target of relentless bullies. With the aid of a sympathetic guidance counselor, Amy explores the meaning of her surreal abilities and discovers her place in the world.
Deluxe Official Handbook containing profiles on characters listed from Cloak to Doctor Octopus.
name: Cloak To Doctor Octopus

concept_credits.name: Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe

first_appearance_concepts.name: Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe

volume.name: The Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe

description:
Overview

The event of the year is here! This brand-new, year-long weekly series features a cast of hundreds where anything goes! With head writer Paul Dini and a rotating team of some of the industry's best writers and artists, COUNTDOWN will serve as the backbone of the DCU in 2007.

When a character dies in COUNTDOWN 51, it sets off an unexpected ripple that will touch virtually every character in the DC Universe.

The COUNTDOWN is on…so begins the end!

Desaad ponders the worth of life as he continues to torture another helpless victim. Darkseid comes in, looking over a table with figurines of the heroes and villains of Earth. He notes that the time will soon come when everything will be recreated and it is he who will shape the way things turn out.

On Earth, Duela Dent, the self-proclaimed daughter of the Joker, is at a night club. She spots a teen pop idol, grabs her, and makes an exit. She tells the singer to have her manager deliver ten million dollars or she will die. As they parachute out the window of the club, Duela's parachute is shot at. She drops the singer in order to save herself. Landing on another roof top, she soon sees the Red Hood with the singer in his arms.

After some talk, Duela jumps off the roof with the remains of her parachute. Red Hood again shoots at it, causing Duela to grab onto a nearby pipe. She is getting tired of this and decides to run from Red Hood.

In the hospital, Mary Batson is finally released after coming out of her coma. She is upset that no one was there for her or now that she is being released. She finds out that the hospital costs were covered by Freddy Freeman. He stopped by the hospital to pay her bill and left a note that said, "Mary, Don't try to find me." The week that she's been out of her coma, she's tried saying "Shazam" with no results. Outside the hospital, she says it again. The only thing that happens is it starts to rain. Probably just a coincidence, she figures. She knows she's without her power but that doesn't make her helpless. She is determined to find Freddy.

At the criminal Heat Wave's place, Trickster arrives for a gathering, even though he wasn't invited. Heat Wave is reluctant to trust him since he recently sided with Flash against them. Trickster says he's thinking clearly now and just wants to help give Flash a beatdown. On top of the roof, Pied Piper had a rat spying on them. He is surprised to see Trickster up to something. He comments that if the Rogues are up to something, he will not allow Trickster to get in his way.

Duela continues to run from Red Hood. She is surprised when a blast almost hits her. She didn't think Jason Todd would try to kill her. She turns around and fires a spray taser at him. The shock is sent back to her. She finds that it is not the Red Hood trying to kill her but rather a man in shadows. He says her presence in this world will not be tolerated. She belongs to another "Earth" and must face the penalty of death for being here. Red Hood comes to her rescue, not being fond of "gun-wielding crazies."

Standing before Red Hood is a Monitor. Red Hood asks what he is and the Monitor replies, "The Multiverse's only hope." He turns around and shoots Duela with his gun. Red Hood attacks the Monitor. The Monitor says that Duela was a threat to the sanctity of the multiverse and had to be purged. He is about to purge Jason too when another Monitor arrives. He tells the first that he is out of his jurisdiction. He acted without authority. The first Monitor says he didn't need any to take out "vermin" and teleports away. Looking at Duela, the second just says he is sorry. Jason reaches for Duela to find her, apparently, dead.

The Monitor travels to the Source Wall seeking the answers he needs. He mentions the tension in the multiverse they have detected recently and asks why it is happening. The response is "Great Disaster." The Monitor figures this means the end of time that was foretold is approaching. He asks for more information, how can the end be prevented, what is the solution? Their response to this is . This seems to surprise the Monitor.
name: Look to the Skies

description:
Overview

Three friends are dead, and as Nightwing's thirst for revenge grows, he finds himself having to choose a path that could alter his future forever. Also, 300 hundred years ago an evil was born, and now, to survive, it is ready to destroy in the conclusion of "Bride and Groom."
name: Bride and Groom, Part 4

description:
Diana and I-Ching attempt to infiltrate Cyber's base of operations.

Diana attempts to rescue Tim Trench from Doctor Cyber's underwater lair and their pursuit of her takes them to Switzerland.
name: The Wrath of Dr. Cyber!

description: Trench takes the treasure Cyber offered and runs, leaving Diana and Ching to fight off Cyber's falcons.
name: A Time to Love, a Time to Die!

description:
The Amazon emissary locates Diana and I-Ching and brings them both across dimensional barriers to the land where Paradise Island now exists.

Diana returns home to Paradise Island to find her mother permanently asleep due to a magical spell which one of Ares' minions has cast on her. He is seeking that she hand over her ring for dimensional travel. Diana decides to lead the Amazons into battle, first against a horde of monsters and later to rescue her kidnapped mother.
name: Return to Paradise Island!

description:
Diana travels to another dimension where King Arthur and heroes of legend still exist and asks for their help in repelling Mars’s troops.

Diana goes to recruit heroes of lore to aid her in the defense of Paradise Island but does not get the help she expects. She returns to defend her home from the invaders.
name: The Last Battle!

description:
Diana discovers that a girl is hiding out from a trio of women whose leader seeks to bring her back as a collared slave.

Diana and a young runaway she takes in are terrorized by THEM!
name: Them!

description: Diana introduces I-Ching to all her new friends. The next day, she receives a substantial reward from Mr. Smithson, the victim of Top Hat's jewel robbery, and uses it to rebuild her boutique in style.
name: Morgana The Witch!

description:
I-Ching receives a call from an old friend in Hong Kong, asking for help.

I-Ching and Diana are brought to Hong Kong to face a threat from Doctor Cyber
name: Earth-Quaker! - Part One

description: Selina must bring herself perilously close to capture or even death as she tries to free a convicted killer from Death's Row. Who is this alleged criminal, and what could bring Catwoman to risk everything she's gained to free them from Gotham's "finest?" The answer lies buried somewhere in Selina's past.
name: Joy Ride

description: Cameron Stewart takes over the art chores as we begin a devastating new arc in the life of Selina Kyle! Selina sets out to give something back to the neighborhood, but a new wave of crime brings her even closer to her roots than she ever imagined. And if that weren’t enough, wait’ll you learn the startling secret one of our supporting cast members is carrying. Plus, hold on to your seats as a surprise character appears to shake things up! This issue’s got it all, including Slam Bradley, Leslie Thompkins, and even Bruce Wayne!
name: Final Report

description: Cameron Stewart takes over the art chores as we begin a devastating new arc in the life of Selina Kyle! Selina sets out to give something back to the neighborhood, but a new wave of crime brings her even closer to her roots than she ever imagined. And if that weren't enough, wait'll you learn the startling secret one of our supporting cast members is carrying. Plus, hold on to your seats as a surprise character appears to shake things up! This issue's got it all, including Slam Bradley, Leslie Thompkins, and even Bruce Wayne!
name: Relentless, Part One

description: Selina presents a very special gift to the East End in while Slam Bradley displays his darker side. Holly rocks to her favorite band while a very deadly plan is put into motion, one that targets not just Catwoman, but Selina Kyle as well.
name: Relentless, Part Two

description: Catwoman's world is falling apart! As her good works in Gotham crumble, readers learn which close friend of Selina's was behind the recent destruction. And Slam Bradley meets with a most unfortunate fate, knock-knock-knockin' on heaven's door. All of this is pushing Holly to the edge, and time is running out for her sanity.
name: Relentless, Part Three

description: The penultimate chapter of the current story arc finds those closest to Selina Kyle meeting terrible fates! While one of her oldest friends schemes against her, Catwoman races to save her sister from the clutches of the Black Mask.
name: Relentless, Part Four

description: A most disturbing Catwoman story comes to a definitive,and deadly,conclusion! The fates of those closest to Selina are resolved, but now her future is in question. Black Mask has struck back at Catwoman in every way possible. Now the Feline Fatale is on a one-way, high-impact course of revenge, but Black Mask is waiting for Catwoman, and he's getting help from someone very close to her!
name: Relentless, Part Five

description: In the aftermath of her final battle with the Black Mask, the lives of Catwoman and those closest to her lie in ruins. Selina has fallen victim to her own sense of defeat; Slam Bradley is beaten, battered and out of commission; Holly is on the verge of falling back into drugs; and, as for Selina's sister, Maggie…well, let's just say Maggie isn't doing too well.
name: No Easy Way Down, Part One

description: The 3-part "No Easy Way Down" continues! Catwoman's still keeping the people in Gotham's forgotten neighborhoods safe, but without anything in her personal life as Selina Kyle to keep her going, she becomes more dangerous to herself and the people around her. It'll take everything she has to see the light at the end of the tunnel, and her apathy could have dire consequences.
name: No Easy Way Down, Part Two

description: The conclusion to "No Easy Way Down!" Brutal truths are revealed and pivotal decisions are made as Slam Bradley finally resolves the case of the Missing Goldigger with gory results. Meanwhile, Selina reaches some devastating conclusions about herself, Holly makes a decision that could plunge her back into the dark world of drug addiction, and Slam makes the hardest choice of his life.
name: No Easy Way Down, Part Three

description: Selina and Holly hit the road to see the world, rediscover themselves, and track down a very important figure from Holly's past. Their first stop takes them to upstate New York, where they have a not-so-chance encounter with the JSA's Wildcat! But as he shows Holly the ropes, an item of great value lures Catwoman into a mysterious world of intrigue and danger.
name: Wild Ride, Part 1: Other Cats

description: Selina and Holly continue their road trip with a stop in Keystone City. It's supposed to be a simple vacation, until a member of The Flash's Rogue's Gallery blackmails Selina into helping him pull off a major score. And with Captain Cold on one side and the law on the other, how can Catwoman escape unscathed?
name: Wild Ride, Part 2: Cold Day In Hell

description: Catwoman's road trip has brought her to the underworld of Keystone City and an unlikely pairing with Captain Cold. The only way she can get the info she needs out of the rogue is to aid him in a quest that will take them deep into the Flash legacy.
name: Wild Ride, Part Three: Meanwhile

description: Catwoman's road trip continues with a stop in a Opal City. Danger is everywhere as Arabian ninjas who plagued Selina back in Keystone City catch up with her and Holly.
name: Wild Ride, Part Four: Opal After Night

description: Selina and Holly's "Wild Ride" comes to its conclusion in Hawkman's and Hawkgirl's St. Roch. A recent threat is explained while new questions are raised.
name: Wild Ride, Part Five: History

description: Things in East End have taken a turn for the worse, and a gang war is brewing.
name: Fire With Fire

description:
Selina's plan to take back the East End from the Mob hits a snag when an innocent girl is kidnapped. But was the kidnapping staged to lure Catwoman into the open?

Note: New art team
name: A Knife in the Dark

description: Selina crosses paths with the Dark Knight as she scours the East End for the mastermind behind the brutal kidnapping that put one of her friends in the hospital. Will these uneasy allies be able to work together, or will Catwoman go her own way?
name: Night Moves

description: Selina squares off with the Penguin in her hunt for the mysterious villain who's dogging her steps. But will she get the information she seeks? Or will she walk into the Penguin's trap?
name: Miss Calculating

description: Selina Kyle has met a foe she can't bring down on her own. So where will she turn for help? And just when she doesn't need any more trouble, she realizes that someone is watching her, and her closest friends are nowhere to be found!
name: Under Pressure

description: Place your bets— the climactic battle between Catwoman and Zeiss happens here! With all her friends deserting her and the East End slipping through her grasp, can Selina survive a rooftop showdown with a villain who once fought Batman to a standstill?
name: End of the Line

description: 2 of 2. After the violent and confusing events of issue one, twins Eve and Lola decide to hunt down some answers. While Eve finally meets her maker - genius scientist Dr Chandelier - Lola meets her biggest crush, a singer named Al Roma.
name: Deuces Wild

description: Why can't Donna just tell her story? Her therapist can't decide what's going on since the story changes every time she hears it. Who's driving...where are they driving to...who's in the back seat with Donna? Is Donna lying to her therapist...or herself? And what did Cindy do to the guy who took her place?

The dramatic conclusion to Sam Kieth's chilling series answers many of our questions, as Donna comes clean with her therapist. Have you guessed what really happened in the car on the way to the wedding? In that car, on that day, would you have fought for survival or friendship? Forgiveness sometimes comes from the place you least expect it. Even through a locked door...if you're lucky.
